n, ob dem Kreditgeber hierdurch bestimmte Pflichten erwachsen und Haftungs- bzw. Anfechtungsrisiken drohen.  aThis work examines the effects of covenants on the position of creditors and their claims for credit in the event of debtor insolvency. In addition, the study examines the question whether any specific obligations arise for the creditor in this situation and whether the creditor faces any threat of liability risks or legal challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aInsolvenz /Recht. 7aLAW / Civil Procedure.2bisacsh  aInsolvency / Law.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2013z9783110317190oZDB-23-DGC0 cprintz978311031505940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311031515840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110315158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110315158/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2013  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014